article.headline: Binghamton 71, North Florida 64
article.story: VESTAL, N.Y. (AP) -- Andre Heard scored 20 of his 26 points in the second half to lead Binghamton to a 71-64 win over North Florida Saturday. Sebastian Hermenier added 24 points and 10 rebounds for the Bearcats (2-6), who took their first lead of the game on Troy Hailey's 3-pointer with two minutes remaining. The Bearcats, down by as many as 12 points, trailed 60-55 with four minutes left before getting 3-pointers on three consecutive possessions. After North Florida (3-4) missed a layup, Binghamton made seven free throws to seal the win. The Bearcats closed the game on a 20-6 run. Hermenier was 9-of-10 from the field and posted his second straight double-double. Alain Laroche led the Ospreys with 23 points and 10 rebounds. Chris Timberlake scored 12 points and Rashad Williams had 11.
